Package gw.plugin.policy.refresh.ui

Class EntityDiffDisplay<T extends KeyableBean>

java.lang.Object
gw.api.bean.compare.ui.BaseEntityDiffDisplay<T>
gw.plugin.policy.refresh.ui.EntityDiffDisplay<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
DiffDisplay, HierarchicalDiff<DiffDisplay>, DiffDisplay
public class EntityDiffDisplay<T extends KeyableBean> extends BaseEntityDiffDisplay<T> implements DiffDisplay, HierarchicalDiff<DiffDisplay>
Superclass for displaying entity diffs in the policy refresh comparison UI. This class can be used as is or subclassed by customers to give control over the UI or to add errors and warnings. If customers do not specify any particular EntityDiff type for an entity type then this is the type that will be used by default.

    • isChildVisible

      protected boolean isChildVisible(DiffDisplay child)
      Called by the default implementation of getVisibleChildren() to determine whether a child in the should be part of the visible list. The default implementation returns true; subclasses can override this method to hide particular children in the policy comparison UI. Note that if a subclass completely overrides the default implementation of getVisibleChildren() then this method will no longer be called (unless the overridden implementation calls it explicitly)
      Parameters:
      child - the child
      Returns:
      true if the child should be visible in the UI, false otherwise

    • getMessages

      public UIMessageList getMessages(PolicyRefreshMessageContext ctx)
      Provides the List of displayable messages (errors, warnings) related to this Diff. The default implementation returns a new, empty message list. Subclasses can override this method to construct appropriate errors and warnings if the underlying difference in the policy comparison is problematic.
